description.displayText: Annie has been with our almost 4 year old for almost 2 years and has been above and beyond what we had expected. Our son has been going through early intervention for some development delays and Annie really took it upon herself to help with his therapies. She regularly participated in them and continued to work with him at home. Specifically with activities of daily living, she personally is responsible for taking him from well below average to now meeting expectations! And, of course, she is always punctual, has almost never called out, and become an integral part of our family. Our son is starting full time preschool soon and it doesn't make sense for her or us to continue so we reluctantly have to say goodbye.

description.displayText: We had a golden month with Andrea! She took care of our 5-month old son when we needed temporary child-care and she did an excellent job. First of all, she took care of our son like he was her own, thinking of activities for him, worrying about his health, and even following up to ask about how things went with our pediatrician.  Second of all, as we are first time parents, she told us about useful products and toys we could buy. For example, she anticipated ahead because our son was teething and suggested we buy bibs to keep his clothes dry.  Andrea was also extraordinarily helpful around the house. We asked her to do some light housework but, while the baby was sleeping, she managed to reorganize our kitchen, keep it spotless, clean the baby room and his toys and do the baby's laundry. I am experimenting with cloth diapers and she even washed the dirty cloth diapers! She is a self-starter, takes initiative and can add value beyond what is just asked.   I highly recommend her!!

description.displayText:
Andrea "Annie" is absolutely incredible. She gained our trust, love & admiration within a few days of employment (as nanny to our 4 year-old son) & quickly became part of our family. I can honestly say that I love this woman. 

She cooks, cleans, educates, politely disciplines, & became a true friend. Annie emits nothing but positive energy and creativity. We never had to inform or suggest things for her to do with our son during the day. She'd take him to the park, museums, arrange play dates, and deplete as much energy out of my son (to help him wind down for the night). She found endless things for them to do and kept him safe and encouraged healthy habits, including home-cooked meals! 

Annie would help with his reading, writing, cooking, activities, creativity, and even helped potty train our son! When we came home from work, our son was fed, bathed and ready for bed. Whatever they "used" was cleaned thoroughly before our arrival home. She will be a great addition to your family!

description.displayText: My husband and I interviewed Andrea and we were very impressed. She arrived on time and was pleasant and professional. Andrea is clearly knowledgeable about childcare for a range of ages, and has creative and thoughtful ideas about ways to engage children and help them learn and grow. I even saw a glowing post about Andrea by her current employer, on a local parents' online group I am part of! We ultimately decided to go in another direction, but I would feel very comfortable if my child was in Andrea's care.

description.displayText: Andrea has been the nanny for our two boys for the past 4 years, starting when our oldest was 2 and youngest was just born. In that time she has become an invaluable member of our household parenting team, and someone that I trust implicitly; not only with my children's safety, but their development and happiness.  Andrea has been a perfect fit for every stage of my kid's lives so far. She's knowledgeable and loving with newborns, and playful yet firm with toddlers and preschoolers. She keeps the kids moving and engaged, and has instilled in them beautiful manners. She's made friends with many of the kid's classmate's caregivers and is always setting up play dates.  Andrea keeps our apartment tidy, handles the children's laundry and fixes them healthy lunches every day. And she does all this with hardly any guidance from me, which, as a mom, is a true luxury - not having to come up with a plan! Andrea's extensive experience and dedication to her work make her a true asset to a family!

description.displayText: Andrea was our nanny from the time my son was three months old until he was 10 months and we moved away from the area. She is an exceptional care giver: my son was immaculate, he learned how to eat well and sleep on a schedule and she constantly kept him engaged with books, singing and blocks. Anyone would be lucky to have her in their household.

description.displayText: Andrea is an excellent childcare provider. She cared for my toddler, and she went beyond her daily responsibilities. Without being prompted, she would read stories and sing nursery rhymes to my daughter.  Also, Andrea is a very prompt person. Always, even in terrible weather, showed up to work on time. As a school social worker and a mother of four, I strongly recommend Andrea.

description.displayText: Andrea is nothing short of amazing. When Andrea first started with us, my daughter was 3 months old and EBF. Despite my efforts, she would not take a bottle. I was a wreck. Andrea was calm and patient yet persistent. She taught my daughter how to take the bottle within the first day. She is smart, alert, and picked up on things with my daughter before I did. She really knows her stuff! Andrea took initiative and got to know others in the building and the area right away. She arranged play dates and group outings. She took my daughter to story time at the library, to the park, and to any classes we had signed her up for.
